The paper deals with knowledge base embedding, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) that involves representing and learning from structured knowledge. The paper also involves developing new models for this task, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The use of knowledge bases and the need to represent multi-fold relations also suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, such as converting multi-fold relations to triples, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
